Package com.rapidminer.belt.column

Class Dictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rapidminer.belt.column.Dictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Dictionary.Entry>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanDictionary
    public class Dictionary
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Dictionary.Entry>
    A dictionary is a one-to-one mapping of category indices to distinct String values. Returns null for unknown indices such as CategoricalReader.MISSING_CATEGORY. All known indices are mapped to distinct object values.

    In case it has at most two non-null object values, a dictionary can be boolean, see isBoolean().

    Author:
    Gisa Meier

        public int maximalIndex()
        Returns the maximal category index that is associated to an object or 0. Note that not every category index below the maximal index must have an associated object value, there can be gaps.
        Returns:
